Uh...but...

2882
01:52:13,300 --> 01:52:16,300
And we catch the universe as it's expanding.

2883
01:52:16,300 --> 01:52:18,300
There's no doubt of that.

2884
01:52:18,300 --> 01:52:20,300
The issue is not whether it's expanding now or not,

2885
01:52:20,300 --> 01:52:22,300
or what we see when we look out.

2886
01:52:22,300 --> 01:52:23,800
The issue is if we

2887
01:52:23,800 --> 01:52:25,300
wait long enough into the future,

2888
01:52:25,300 --> 01:52:26,800
will everything turn around and

2889
01:52:26,800 --> 01:52:28,300
crash back on top of us?

2890
01:52:28,300 --> 01:52:32,300
And if there was no vacuum energy...

2891
01:52:32,300 --> 01:52:34,300
If there were no vacuum energy,

2892
01:52:34,300 --> 01:52:35,300
then the answer would be,

2893
01:52:35,300 --> 01:52:38,300
if the universe were positively curved,

2894
01:52:38,300 --> 01:52:41,300
it would collapse back on itself.

2895
01:52:41,300 --> 01:52:43,300
Uh...the vacuum energy,

2896
01:52:43,300 --> 01:52:45,300
if it's large enough, will prevent that.

2897
01:52:45,300 --> 01:52:48,300
And it certainly does look large enough.

2898
01:52:48,300 --> 01:52:50,300
So it looks like our future,

2899
01:52:50,300 --> 01:52:52,300
independently of whether we're curved

2900
01:52:52,300 --> 01:52:53,800
or whether we're positively

2901
01:52:53,800 --> 01:52:55,300
curved, negatively curved, or flat,

2902
01:52:55,300 --> 01:52:58,300
it looks like our future is one in which

2903
01:52:58,300 --> 01:53:01,300
the universe will simply exponentially expand.

2904
01:53:01,300 --> 01:53:03,300
Now, that's not such a good thing either.

2905
01:53:03,300 --> 01:53:04,300
If it exponentially...

2906
01:53:04,300 --> 01:53:07,300
It's not a good future in any case.

2907
01:53:07,300 --> 01:53:11,300
If it exponentially expands,

2908
01:53:11,300 --> 01:53:14,300
eventually all the stars will burn out,

2909
01:53:14,300 --> 01:53:16,300
everything will cool down,

2910
01:53:16,300 --> 01:53:18,300
everything will dilute,

2911
01:53:18,300 --> 01:53:21,300
all ordinary forms of energy will exponentially dilute,

2912
01:53:21,300 --> 01:53:24,300
because if the universe is exponentially expanding,

2913
01:53:24,300 --> 01:53:27,300
its volume is exponentially expanding,

2914
01:53:27,300 --> 01:53:29,300
all the energy densities of all the other kinds,

2915
01:53:29,300 --> 01:53:31,300
other than the vacuum energy,

2916
01:53:31,300 --> 01:53:32,300
will expand.

2917
01:53:32,300 --> 01:53:34,300
All the energy densities of all the other kinds,

2918
01:53:34,300 --> 01:53:36,300
other than the vacuum energy density,

2919
01:53:36,300 --> 01:53:38,300
will also exponentially dilute,

2920
01:53:38,300 --> 01:53:40,300
and will just be in

2921
01:53:40,300 --> 01:53:42,300
a universe with nothing in it,

2922
01:53:42,300 --> 01:53:46,300
or with thinner and thinner energy density.

2923
01:53:46,300 --> 01:53:50,300
So there is no good end to this story.

2924
01:53:50,300 --> 01:53:54,300
Also, a great distance away from us,

2925
01:53:54,300 --> 01:53:57,300
will there be an increased amount of photons,

2926
01:53:57,300 --> 01:54:00,300
because in the early universe,

2927
01:54:00,300 --> 01:54:03,300
it was dominated by photons,

2928
01:54:03,300 --> 01:54:06,300
and the universe expands.

2929
01:54:06,300 --> 01:54:12,300
Since the photons move faster than, say, the mass,

2930
01:54:12,300 --> 01:54:14,300
the matter that was in there,

2931
01:54:14,300 --> 01:54:16,300
what do you expect?

2932
01:54:16,300 --> 01:54:19,300
As you look back into the past,

2933
01:54:19,300 --> 01:54:25,300
the ratio of photons to ordinary particles,

2934
01:54:25,300 --> 01:54:29,300
well, let's see how to say it.

2935
01:54:29,300 --> 01:54:31,800
I would say more than

2936
01:54:31,800 --> 01:54:34,300
saying that the number of photons

2937
01:54:34,300 --> 01:54:38,300
doesn't get larger than the number of...

2938
01:54:38,300 --> 01:54:40,300
It's already true in our universe

2939
01:54:40,300 --> 01:54:42,300
that the number of photons is much, much larger

2940
01:54:42,300 --> 01:54:44,300
than the number of atoms.

2941
01:54:44,300 --> 01:54:47,300
Ten to the tenth times larger.

2942
01:54:47,300 --> 01:54:49,300
So we are dominated by photons.

2943
01:54:49,300 --> 01:54:51,300
I don't mean the photons from light bulbs,

2944
01:54:51,300 --> 01:54:53,300
I don't mean the photons from the sun,

2945
01:54:53,300 --> 01:54:55,300
I don't mean the photons from stars,

2946
01:54:55,300 --> 01:54:58,300
I mean the microwave background from the Big Bang.

2947
01:54:59,300 --> 01:55:04,300
We are certainly dominated by photons.

2948
01:55:04,300 --> 01:55:06,300
Now as you go back in time,

2949
01:55:06,300 --> 01:55:11,300
the ratio of photons to protons stays about the same.

2950
01:55:11,300 --> 01:55:14,300
But the photons get more and more energetic

2951
01:55:14,300 --> 01:55:16,300
and the protons don't.

2952
01:55:16,300 --> 01:55:19,300
So as far as energy goes,

2953
01:55:19,300 --> 01:55:21,300
as you go back into the past,

2954
01:55:21,300 --> 01:55:24,300
the energy will be dominated by the photons.

2955
01:55:24,300 --> 01:55:27,300
The number of photons will stay the same,

2956
01:55:27,300 --> 01:55:28,300
but their energy will increase

2957
01:55:28,300 --> 01:55:30,300
as you go back into the past.

2958
01:55:30,300 --> 01:55:32,300
The number of protons will stay the same,

2959
01:55:32,300 --> 01:55:34,300
but their energy won't increase,

2960
01:55:34,300 --> 01:55:39,300
or at least not as fast.

2961
01:55:39,300 --> 01:55:41,300
Good. Okay.

2962
01:55:41,300 --> 01:55:44,300
I'm tired. Let's go home.

2963
